### Pancake Order Sync & Webhook Testing
### Use REST Client extension in VS Code

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3001
@adminToken = your-admin-jwt-token-here
@webhookUrl = https://your-domain.com/integrations/pancake/webhook

### ========================================
### MANUAL SYNC
### ========================================

### 1. Sync All Orders (No filters)
POST {{baseUrl}}/integrations/pancake/sync-all-orders
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### 2. Sync Orders with Date Range
POST {{baseUrl}}/integrations/pancake/sync-all-orders
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "startDate": "2024-01-01",
  "endDate": "2024-01-31"
}

### 3. Sync Orders for Specific Store
POST {{baseUrl}}/integrations/pancake/sync-all-orders
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "storeId": "your-store-uuid-here"
}

### ========================================
### WEBHOOK CONFIGURATION
### ========================================

### 4. Configure Webhook on Pancake
POST {{baseUrl}}/integrations/pancake/configure-webhook
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "webhookUrl": "{{webhookUrl}}",
  "webhookTypes": ["orders", "customers"]
}

### 5. Get Current Webhook Configuration
POST {{baseUrl}}/integrations/pancake/webhook-config
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

### ========================================
### WEBHOOK TESTING (Simulate Pancake)
### ========================================

### 6. Test Webhook - New Order
POST {{baseUrl}}/integrations/pancake/webhook
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "type": "orders",
  "data": {
    "id": 9999,
    "shop_id": 4,
    "system_id": 1,
    "inserted_at": "2024-01-15T10:30:00",
