### ========================================
### OTHER SYNC ENDPOINTS (Already Implemented)
### ========================================

### 10. Sync Categories
POST {{baseUrl}}/integrations/pancake/sync-categories
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

### 11. Sync Products
POST {{baseUrl}}/integrations/pancake/sync-products
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "storeId": "optional-store-uuid"
}

### 12. Sync Orders for Specific User (Old endpoint)
POST {{baseUrl}}/integrations/pancake/sync-orders
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone": "0999999999",
  "userId": "user-uuid-here"
}

### ========================================
### NOTES
### ========================================

# 1. Replace {{adminToken}} with actual JWT token from admin login
# 2. Replace {{webhookUrl}} with your actual webhook URL
# 3. For production, use ngrok to test webhook:
#    ngrok http 3001
#    Then use: https://your-ngrok-url.ngrok.io/integrations/pancake/webhook
# 
# 4. Pancake webhook will send POST requests automatically when:
#    - New order created
#    - Order status updated
#    - Customer created/updated
#    - Product created/updated
#    - Inventory updated
#
# 5. Check logs for webhook processing:
#    npm run start:dev | grep "Pancake"
